{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":578,"text":"Well, I was introduced as"},{"time":3496,"text":"the former Governor of Michigan,"},{"time":5528,"text":"but actually I'm a scientist."},{"time":8544,"text":"All right, a political scientist, it doesn't really count,"},{"time":11536,"text":"but my laboratory was the laboratory of democracy"},{"time":15332,"text":"that is Michigan, and, like any good scientist,"},{"time":18488,"text":"I was experimenting with policy"},{"time":21330,"text":"about what would achieve the greatest good"},{"time":24024,"text":"for the greatest number."},{"time":26133,"text":"But there were three problems, three enigmas"},{"time":30411,"text":"that I could not solve,"},{"time":32945,"text":"and I want to share with you those problems,"},{"time":36423,"text":"but most importantly,"},{"time":38429,"text":"I think I figured out a proposal for a solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42185,"text":"The first problem"},{"time":44054,"text":"that not just Michigan, but every state, faces is,"},{"time":46045,"text":"how do you create good jobs in America"},{"time":49364,"text":"in a global economy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51112,"text":"So let me share with you some empirical data from my lab."},{"time":54604,"text":"I was elected in 2002 and, at the end of my first year in office in 2003,"},{"time":59114,"text":"I got a call from one of my staff members, who said,"},{"time":61646,"text":"\"Gov, we have a big problem."},{"time":64014,"text":"We have a little tiny community called Greenville, Michigan,"},{"time":67634,"text":"population 8,000,"},{"time":69896,"text":"and they are about to lose their major employer,"},{"time":72691,"text":"which is a refrigerator factory that's operated by Electrolux.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":77510,"text":"And I said, \"Well, how many people work at Electrolux?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":80189,"text":"And he said, \"3,000 of the 8,000 people in Greenville.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":85119,"text":"So it is a one-company town."},{"time":87900,"text":"And Electrolux was going to go to Mexico."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92828,"text":"So I said, \"Forget that. I'm the new Governor."},{"time":95716,"text":"We can fix this. We're going to go to Greenville"},{"time":98004,"text":"with my whole cabinet and we will just"},{"time":99972,"text":"make Electrolux an offer they can't refuse.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":102877,"text":"So I brought my whole cabinet,"},{"time":105308,"text":"and we met with all of the pooh-bahs of little Greenville --"},{"time":109020,"text":"the mayor, the city manager, the head of the community college --"},{"time":112250,"text":"and we basically emptied our pockets"},{"time":115845,"text":"and put all of our chips on the table,"},{"time":119138,"text":"incentives, you name it, to convince Electrolux to stay,"},{"time":123266,"text":"and as we made our pile of chips,"},{"time":124917,"text":"we slid them across the table to the management of Electrolux."},{"time":130024,"text":"And in the pile were things like zero taxes for 20 years,"},{"time":134132,"text":"or that we'd help to build a new factory for the company,"},{"time":138348,"text":"we'd help to finance it. The UAW, who represented the workers,"},{"time":141141,"text":"said they would offer unprecedented concessions,"},{"time":144980,"text":"sacrifices to just keep those jobs in Greenville."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149033,"text":"So the management of Electrolux took our pile,"},{"time":151911,"text":"our list of incentives, and they went outside the room"},{"time":154724,"text":"for 17 minutes,"},{"time":157244,"text":"and they came back in and they said,"},{"time":159475,"text":"\"Wow, this is the most generous"},{"time":162416,"text":"any community has ever been to try to keep jobs here."},{"time":166905,"text":"But there's nothing you can do"},{"time":170300,"text":"to compensate for the fact that we can pay $1.57 an hour"},{"time":174589,"text":"in Juarez, Mexico. So we're leaving.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":177847,"text":"And they did. And when they did, it was like"},{"time":180852,"text":"a nuclear bomb went off in little Greenville."},{"time":184108,"text":"In fact, they did implode the factory."},{"time":186423,"text":"That's a guy that is walking on his last day of work."},{"time":190401,"text":"And on the month that the last refrigerator rolled off the assembly line,"},{"time":194425,"text":"the employees of Electrolux in Greenville, Michigan,"},{"time":197065,"text":"had a gathering for themselves that they called the last supper."},{"time":202730,"text":"It was in a big pavilion in Greenville, an indoor pavilion,"},{"time":205713,"text":"and I went to it because I was so frustrated as Governor"},{"time":210202,"text":"that I couldn't stop the outflow of these jobs,"},{"time":214099,"text":"and I wanted to grieve with them,"},{"time":216622,"text":"and as I went into the room-- there's thousands of people there."},{"time":219942,"text":"It was a just big thing. People were eating boxed lunches"},{"time":223685,"text":"on roundtop tables, and there was a sad band playing music,"},{"time":227845,"text":"or a band playing sad music, probably both. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":231582,"text":"And this guy comes up to me,"},{"time":234809,"text":"and he's got tattoos and his ponytail and his baseball cap on,"},{"time":238549,"text":"and he had his two daughters with him,"},{"time":241167,"text":"and he said, \"Gov, these are my two daughters.\""},{"time":244774,"text":"He said, \"I'm 48 years old,"},{"time":247822,"text":"and I have worked at this factory for 30 years."},{"time":252380,"text":"I went from high school to factory."},{"time":255036,"text":"My father worked at this factory,\" he said."},{"time":257644,"text":"\"My grandfather worked at this factory."},{"time":260493,"text":"All I know is how to make refrigerators.\""},{"time":265516,"text":"And he looked at his daughters,"},{"time":266869,"text":"and he puts his hand on his chest,"},{"time":269357,"text":"and he says, \"So, Gov, tell me,"},{"time":271907,"text":"who is ever going to hire me?"},{"time":277235,"text":"Who is ever going to hire me?\""},{"time":280668,"text":"And that was asked not just by that guy"},{"time":284190,"text":"but by everyone in the pavilion,"},{"time":286868,"text":"and frankly, by every worker at one of the 50,000 factories"},{"time":292708,"text":"that closed in the first decade of this century."},{"time":297020,"text":"Enigma number one: How do you create jobs"},{"time":299914,"text":"in America in a global economy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302347,"text":"Number two, very quickly:"},{"time":304647,"text":"How do you solve global climate change"},{"time":307379,"text":"when we don't even have a national energy policy in this country"},{"time":311716,"text":"and when gridlock in Congress seems to be the norm?"},{"time":316644,"text":"In fact, there was a poll that was done recently"},{"time":319806,"text":"and the pollster compared Congress's approval ratings"},{"time":324083,"text":"to a number of other unpleasant things,"},{"time":326513,"text":"and it was found, in fact, that Congress's approval rating"},{"time":330033,"text":"is worse than cockroaches,"},{"time":332915,"text":"lice, Nickelback the band, root canals and Donald Trump. (Laughter)"},{"time":339907,"text":"But wait, the good news is it's at least better"},{"time":344186,"text":"than meth labs and gonorrhea. (Laughter)"},{"time":349042,"text":"We got a problem, folks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352867,"text":"So it got me thinking, what is it?"},{"time":354505,"text":"What in the laboratory that I see out there,"},{"time":358267,"text":"the laboratories of democracy, what has happened?"},{"time":360417,"text":"What policy prescriptions have happened"},{"time":363116,"text":"that actually cause changes to occur"},{"time":364908,"text":"and that have been accepted in a bipartisan way?"},{"time":368475,"text":"So if I asked you, for example,"},{"time":369753,"text":"what was the Obama Administration policy"},{"time":372233,"text":"that caused massive changes across the country,"},{"time":375347,"text":"what would you say?"},{"time":376635,"text":"You might say Obamacare, except for those were not voluntary changes."},{"time":380430,"text":"As we know, only half the states have opted in."},{"time":382971,"text":"We might say the Recovery Act, but those didn't require policy changes."},{"time":386480,"text":"The thing that caused massive policy changes to occur"},{"time":390831,"text":"was Race to the Top for education."},{"time":393251,"text":"Why? The government put a $4.5 billion pot"},{"time":396493,"text":"and said to the governors across the country, compete for it."},{"time":399939,"text":"Forty-eight governors competed,"},{"time":403115,"text":"convincing 48 state legislatures to essentially"},{"time":406414,"text":"raise standards for high schoolers"},{"time":408700,"text":"so that they all take a college prep curriculum."},{"time":411011,"text":"Forty-eight states opted in, creating a national [education] policy from the bottom up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416397,"text":"So I thought, well, why can't we do something like that"},{"time":419000,"text":"and create a clean energy jobs race to the top?"},{"time":423046,"text":"Because after all, if you look at the context,"},{"time":425397,"text":"1.6 trillion dollars has been invested in the past eight years"},{"time":429375,"text":"from the private sector globally,"},{"time":431317,"text":"and every dollar represents a job,"},{"time":433689,"text":"and where are those jobs going?"},{"time":435284,"text":"Well, they're going to places that have policy, like China."},{"time":437708,"text":"In fact, I was in China to see what they were doing,"},{"time":439730,"text":"and they were putting on a dog-and-pony show for the group that I was with,"},{"time":442438,"text":"and I was standing in the back of the room during one of the demonstrations"},{"time":445441,"text":"and standing next to one of the Chinese officials,"},{"time":447804,"text":"and we were watching, and he says,"},{"time":449466,"text":"\"So, Gov, when do you think the U.S. is going to get national energy policy?\""},{"time":454100,"text":"And I said, \"Oh my God -- Congress, gridlock, who knows?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":457668,"text":"And this is what he did, he goes, he says,"},{"time":461682,"text":"\"Take your time.\""},{"time":464419,"text":"Because they see our passivity as their opportunity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469057,"text":"So what if we decided to create"},{"time":471990,"text":"a challenge to the governors of the country,"},{"time":474689,"text":"and the price to entry into this competition"},{"time":477495,"text":"used the same amount that the bipartisan group approved in Congress"},{"time":481143,"text":"for the Race to the Top for education, 4.5 billion,"},{"time":483833,"text":"which sounds like a lot, but actually it's less than"},{"time":486216,"text":"one tenth of one percent of federal spending."},{"time":488705,"text":"It's a rounding error on the federal side."},{"time":490729,"text":"But price to entry into that competition would be,"},{"time":494647,"text":"you could just, say, use the President's goal."},{"time":497952,"text":"He wants Congress to adopt a clean energy standard"},{"time":501025,"text":"of 80 percent by 2030,"},{"time":503300,"text":"in other words, that you'd have to get 80 percent"},{"time":505279,"text":"of your energy from clean sources by the year 2030."},{"time":508929,"text":"Why not ask all of the states to do that instead?"},{"time":511630,"text":"And imagine what might happen,"},{"time":513621,"text":"because every region has something to offer."},{"time":515609,"text":"You might take states like Iowa and Ohio --"},{"time":518591,"text":"two very important political states, by the way --"},{"time":520608,"text":"those two governors, and they would say,"},{"time":522496,"text":"we're going to lead the nation in producing"},{"time":525211,"text":"the wind turbines and the wind energy."},{"time":527813,"text":"You might say the solar states, the sun belt,"},{"time":530984,"text":"we're going to be the states that produce solar energy for the country,"},{"time":534684,"text":"and maybe Jerry Brown says, \"Well, I'm going to create"},{"time":536854,"text":"an industry cluster in California"},{"time":539031,"text":"to be able to produce the solar panels"},{"time":540870,"text":"so that we're not buying them from China"},{"time":542519,"text":"but we're buying them from the U.S.\""},{"time":544382,"text":"In fact, every region of the country could do this."},{"time":547812,"text":"You see, you've got solar and wind opportunity all across the nation."},{"time":551918,"text":"In fact, if you look just at the upper and northern states"},{"time":555922,"text":"in the West, they could do geothermal,"},{"time":558097,"text":"or you could look at Texas and say,"},{"time":560409,"text":"we could lead the nation in the solutions to smart grid."},{"time":563777,"text":"In the middle eastern states which have access to forests"},{"time":567884,"text":"and to agricultural waste, they might say,"},{"time":570208,"text":"we're going to lead the nation in biofuels."},{"time":572809,"text":"In the upper northeast, we're going to lead the nation"},{"time":575325,"text":"in energy efficiency solutions."},{"time":578189,"text":"Along the eastern seaboard, we're going to lead the nation"},{"time":581158,"text":"in offshore wind."},{"time":582977,"text":"You might look at Michigan and say, we're going to lead the nation"},{"time":585560,"text":"in producing the guts for the electric vehicle, like the lithium ion battery."},{"time":589454,"text":"Every region has something to offer,"},{"time":592861,"text":"and if you created a competition,"},{"time":595183,"text":"it respects the states and it respects federalism."},{"time":599301,"text":"It's opt-in. You might even get Texas and South Carolina,"},{"time":602855,"text":"who didn't opt into the education Race to the Top,"},{"time":605525,"text":"you might even get them to opt in. Why?"},{"time":607926,"text":"Because Republican and Democratic governors"},{"time":610477,"text":"love to cut ribbons."},{"time":612131,"text":"We want to bring jobs. I'm just saying."},{"time":616445,"text":"And it fosters innovation at the state level"},{"time":619065,"text":"in these laboratories of democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621526,"text":"Now, any of you who are watching anything about politics lately"},{"time":625832,"text":"might say, \"Okay, great idea, but really?"},{"time":628589,"text":"Congress putting four and a half billion dollars on the table?"},{"time":631221,"text":"They can't agree to anything.\""},{"time":633494,"text":"So you could wait and go through Congress,"},{"time":636789,"text":"although you should be very impatient."},{"time":639365,"text":"Or, you renegades, we could go around Congress."},{"time":647269,"text":"Go around Congress."},{"time":648827,"text":"What if we created a private sector challenge to the governors?"},{"time":655455,"text":"What if several of the high-net worth companies"},{"time":660415,"text":"and individuals who are here at TED decided"},{"time":664805,"text":"that they would create, band together, just a couple of them,"},{"time":668333,"text":"and create a national competition to the governors"},{"time":671893,"text":"to have a race to the top"},{"time":674149,"text":"and see how the governors respond?"},{"time":676818,"text":"What if it all started here at TED?"},{"time":681706,"text":"What if you were here"},{"time":684365,"text":"when we figured out how to crack the code"},{"time":689713,"text":"to create good paying jobs in America -- (Applause) --"},{"time":695159,"text":"and get national energy policy"},{"time":698880,"text":"and we created a national energy strategy from the bottom up?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":704858,"text":"Because, dear TEDsters,"},{"time":708309,"text":"if you are impatient like I am,"},{"time":711071,"text":"you know that our economic competitors,"},{"time":714629,"text":"our other nations, are in the game"},{"time":718069,"text":"and are eating us for lunch."},{"time":720421,"text":"And we can get in the game or not."},{"time":724967,"text":"We can be at the table or we can be on the table."},{"time":729286,"text":"And I don't know about you,"},{"time":731707,"text":"but I prefer to dine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734414,"text":"Thank you all so much. (Applause)"}]}]}